doc_summary_long: United Nations experts had a damning assessment of taser use in U.S. jails, saying footage they viewed revealed the need for investigations and in some cases showed abusive use of the devices so severe it amounted to torture. The watchdogs viewed video footage obtained by Reuters of 22 incidents in four jails: Franklin County, Ohio; Cheatham County, Tennessee; Franklin County, Arkansas; and McCurtain County, Oklahoma. In addition to showing the need for probe, Nils Melzer, the U.N. special rapporteur on torture, said most of the incidents 'are likely to merit prosecution.'
doc_summary_short: United Nations experts had a damning assessment of taser use in U.S. jails, saying footage they viewed revealed the need for investigations and in some cases showed abusive use of the devices so severe it amounted to torture.
doc_title: UN Experts Say Video Footage of Taser Use in US Jails Reveals Torture
